features: DASH CAM 2K&TWO-FOLD DISCREET DESIGN:This dash camera captures the road at 2K resolution (2560x1600P@30fps) and also record the inside of your vehicle (switch the direction of the dash cam bracket mount). The F1.8 apertures and 6-glass HD lens ensure incredible sharpness and high-quality videos/images, providing four times clearer footage compared to a regular dash cam. It's the ideal choice for you who need to record both the scenery outside and the precious moments spent with your families.

2.5K+1080P DASH CAM FRONT AND REAR:Designed to provide you with unparalleled front and rear recording capabilities. The front camera captures the road ahead in stunning 2.5K resolution, the rear camera records in 1080P resolution. Both capture every moment, protect from potential accidents, and enjoy peace of mind knowing that you have a reliable eyewitness on the road. To ensure distortion-free videos and images, our dash cam utilizes the optimal 140° viewing angle for capturing the road ahead.

WIFI&SMART APP CONTROL: This car camera connect built-in Wifi and the convenience of our DDPAI app, it offers seamless control. Preview, playback, and download videos directly to your smartphone, or effortlessly share incredible HD footage with friends and family. You can even download and edit videos right from the app, allowing you to easily capture and share your travel scenery and unforgettable moments with just a single click.

DASHCAM FRONT AND REAR CAMERA WITH GPS&SR: Our dash cam combines the unique SR 2.0 technology with GPS functionality, providing you with an immersive virtual gaming economy experience. With the integrated GPS, you can track your driving route, monitor your speed and distance ahead and access precise location data. Immerse yourself in a virtual world where you can analyze your driving performance, all while enjoying the peace of mind that comes with reliable and accurate GPS functionality.

RELIABLE WITNESS FOR ACCIDENT:This car dash cam with 24H PARKING MONITOR/G-SENSOR/LOOP RECORDING-Need the hardware kit (which need purchase ASIN:B08NQD7GBG ) for 24 Hours parking mode, which can automatically monitor the surrounding enviroment. When it detects a sudden shock or collision, the camera will automatically loop record driving incidents and lock video as important evidence for insurance claims. (Note: SD car is NOT INCLUDED.)

24-MONTH WARRANTY: This dash camera for cars offering you complete coverage for your car camera. As part of our commitment to excellence, we provide free firmware upgrades to ensure your device is always up to date. Rest assured that this dash camera is backed by a full 2-year warranty, supported by our dedicated customer service team. In the unlikely event of any issues, our professional customer service representatives are available 24/7 to promptly address and resolve any concerns.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Has built in GPS but no night vision.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This is a good little entry level dash cam for cars. I say entry level because it does not have night vision or inside the car recording for the inside portion of the car. It only records outside from the windshield and the rear camera records from the rear outside only and there's no recording for the inside car cabin. Unless you turn the camera around, which is point less because in the dark it does not show anything. The resolution of this camera is pretty good, It records at 2.5K. The built in GPS records the speed limit which is imprinted on the video file along with date time-stamped on the video file. The app can be confusing at first, but the manual explains everything clearly. The rear camera is made of plastic which feels very cheap and clumsy. The front camera has some good weight to it so it feels a bit durable. The length of the wire is pretty good, especially the rear camera, it can be Installed in small cars or SUV's easily. The wire gets connected to a USB port, but If you don't have a USB port, then this camp comes with a cigarette lighter plug that you can plug in the cigarette lighter port. The entire navigation and setting is done through the app on the phone. the camera does not have LCD screen or any buttons, basically every thing is controlled through the app and the app name is DDPAI.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice Dual Camera
reviews.reviewText: So far so good. I've tried out several in the past and never loved one - so far this is my favorite for a few reasons* Came with long enough wiring to run back camera to the front of my Nissan Xterra SUV with no issue - there was spare wire I ended up tucking behind the A Pillar.* "Always On" parking mode which can be turned on or off, and if on has different time out options if you're worried about battery life. In this mode it take snapshots to make a timelapse so you don't get full recording which would kill your battery but you get some insight into what and who was around if a parking lot ding happens. Note that your USB source will need constant power for this to work* multiple levels of sensitivity for the G Sensor "emergency" video save. Normally this is useful if you get hit, bumped or some other jolting action occurs - it automatically saves the video. THe initial setting was too sensitive and crossing highway reflectors would trigger it but I was able to turn it down to only register heavier jolts.* Picture is good. Not the best, but good at this price point*App is decent - not great but gives access to the settings you need, and can also preview videos easily by day and session, then choosing to download any that you want.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The installation was quick and easy and the setup with the app was quick as well. The picture quality is very good both in the daylight and at night. The included GPS also allows for speed indication to be on the recording as well for added safety. The only knock I have with it is the download speed from the camera to your device could be faster.
